      <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-29845438738f42f0a051ae52f98ddbda" font="|9|0" lineColor="#E65100" fillColor="#FFE0B2">
        <bounds x="-34" y="-270" width="900" height="230"/>
        <content>⬆  MERGE → ROOM ACCESS · BUSINESS LAYER  (teammate's diagram)

Wire each Application Service UP to the business process (Serving →):
  • Access Verification Service        →  'Verify Access Authorization'
  • Door Unlock Service                →  'Grant Room Access'
  • Key Card Configuration Service     →  'Issue Key Card' / 'Configure Access Rights'
  • Access Rights Assignment Service   →  'Configure Access Rights'
  • Energy Activation Service          →  'Grant Room Access' (room electricity)

Data alignment (Realization ↑):
  • Access Rights Record  → realizes → 'Access Rights Profile' (BusinessObject)
  • Card Credential       → realizes → 'Key Card' (BusinessObject)

RULE: ApplicationService —Serving→ BusinessProcess  |  DataObject —Realization→ BusinessObject</content>
      </child>
      <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-c5542a5540744d8eb9b2d54c80c4aa25" font="|9|0" lineColor="#E65100" fillColor="#FFE0B2">
        <bounds x="-34" y="790" width="960" height="190"/>
        <content>⬇  MERGE → ROOM ACCESS · TECHNOLOGY LAYER  (teammate's diagram)

Wire each Technology element DOWN to my application elements:
  • 'Door System Software Runtime' (SystemSoftware) on 'Door Control Node'  → realizes →  Door System Software
  • 'Door Card Reader' (Device) via 'RFID Communication' (Network)          → serves   →  Card Reader Interface
  • 'AWS Cloud Server' (Node)                                               → realizes →  Hotel Management System
  • 'Energy Saver Interface' (Device, card switch)                          → serves   →  Energy Management System
  • 'Reception PC &amp; Terminal' (Device)                                      → serves   →  Receptionist Interface

RULE: Node/SystemSoftware —Realization→ ApplicationComponent  |  Device —Serving→ ApplicationComponent/Interface</content>
      </child>
      <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-8b2e5b22bcf144139cde782aa98f6bb3" font="|9|0" lineColor="#6A1B9A" fillColor="#E1BEE7">
        <bounds x="1640" y="120" width="470" height="330"/>
        <content>↔  MERGE → DAILY BRIEFING · APPLICATION LAYER  (teammate's diagram)

SHARED COMPONENT — do NOT duplicate on merge:
  • 'Hotel Management System' in THIS view is the SAME element as the
    'Hotel Management System' in the Daily Briefing app layer.
       – here it performs:  Key Card Configuration Process
       – there it performs: Briefing Report Generation (Compile Briefing Data…)
    → Keep ONE Hotel Management System; attach both processes to it.

SHARED DATA (central HMS / AWS store):
  • Guest profiles &amp; reservations are the same source the briefing reads;
    access rights are assigned from that data at check-in.

NOTE: the PDF describes NO direct service call between the two domains —
they are parallel capabilities running on the one shared HMS platform.
(So the only connector is component identity, not a relationship line.)</content>
      </child>
    </element>
